Brace yourselves, everyone!!! Bad Boys 3 is coming to your screens Will Smith and Martin Lawrence have confirmed that the epic 1995 franchise, Bad Boys For Life is returning. The two will take on their roles as Detectives Mike Lowery and Marcus Burnett in the Sony film. The film’s production is set to kick off in January. According to Deadline, top shots returning include original producer Jerry Bruckheimer and directors Adil El Arbi and Bilall Fallah.   It’s been a LOOOONG time Coming. But now it’s Here! @BadBoys For Life  We back!! @martinlawrence A post shared by  Will Smith (@willsmith) on Nov 1, 2018 at 10:48am PDT 